article_title: Death of man in Carroll County ruled homicide
article_text:
The body of a man found in northern Carroll County has been identified and his death ruled a homicide.

An autopsy done on Prakash Rampatsingh, 50, of Hanover, Pennsylvania, determined he died from a gunshot wound.



Rampatsingh body was found Saturday in the 3200 block of Falls Road in Hampstead, Md.



Police are asking for the public's help in developing information about the case.



If you know anything about the circumstances surrounding Rampatsingh’s death you are asked to call 1-866-7LOCKUP.
